---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import AboutHero from "../components/AboutHero.astro";
import { withBase } from "../utils/url";
---

<Layout title="About" description="About Auto Panda Motive, Pandy's personal garage for car stories and photos.">
  <article class="about-page">
    <AboutHero />
    <div class="container page">
    <h2>Welcome to my garage!</h2>
    <p>
      <em>Auto Panda Motive</em> is my personal garage online: it shares the cars I work on, the stories behind them,
      and the photos along the way.
      Browse <a href={withBase("/garage/")}>The Garage</a> for what I have now, or
      <a href={withBase("/memory-lane/")}>Memory Lane</a> for cars from the past. Each car has its
      own page with photos and a timeline of work and adventures.
      This is not a shop, a business, or a blog. It is a hobby I enjoy sharing with friends, fellow
      enthusiasts, and anyone who wants to know more.
    </p>

    <h2>Why "Auto-Panda-Motive"</h2>
    <p>
      The name is a play on <em><a
        href="https://automationpanda.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">"Automation Panda"</a></em>, my professional moniker for my work in test
      automation and software quality.
      Same panda; different motor.
      Cars and code both reward patience, careful work, and the stubborn satisfaction of fixing something until it runs right.
    </p>

    <h2>Thanks for visiting</h2>
    <p>
      I'm Pandy, a software engineer by trade and a car enthusiast by choice.
      I built this site to share my cool cars and all the stories that go with them.
      Check out the <a href="https://github.com/AutomationPanda/auto-panda-motive"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a> if you want to see how I built the site.
      Thanks for stopping by!
    </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 1.25rem 0 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
